heaviest_rainfall.status: Record amounts of rain fell over 28.2 hours today with a total accumulation of 22.48mm.  It fell at 8.3 mm per hour at times and ranked 7th from our records.  47.89mm of rain was recorded as having fallen on 09 November 2025, marking an exceptional 144.8 hour precipitation event.  At times the rain was falling at 24.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: The storm today ranked 8th for the length of the storm when compared to others in our records and it lasted 28.2 hours.  22.48mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 8.3mm per hour.  Rain fell for 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 47.89mm with a maximum intensity of 24.6mm per hour.
